doCompleteRepaint

boolean doCompleteRepaint
If true, draws all objects in the backup list.

previewObject

PaintObject previewObject
The current preview object. It will be drawn as the top layer each time the component is painted.

ingoing

java.util.Vector<E> ingoing
A list of paint objects that were added to the paint board after the last call to PaintBoard.updateBoard(). The elements of this list will be drawn and added to the backup list.

backup

java.util.Vector<E> backup
A list of all paint objects that were added to the paint board. This list is used in the case of a complete redraw.

cache

java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentLinkedQueue<E> cache
A cache of paint objects. They will be drawn as the top layer each time the component is painted. If an equal new paint object is added via the PaintBoard.add(PaintObject) method, the object is removed from the cache.
